



Sir,
Mount Vernon May 1st 1774



Inclosed you have Bills on Messrs Osgood Hanbury & Co. for One hundred and Ten pounds Sterlg which be so good as to apply in discharge of payment for the Servants you obligingly bought for me.1
I really forgot to send these Bills by the last Post, but hope they are not much out of time now. Be pleased to let the Inclosed
[45]
Letter of advice accompany the Bills, and accept my hearty thanks for the trouble you have had in this affair & be assured that I am Dr Sir Yr Most Obedt Servt

Go: Washington

